In [6]:
# Drop all brand name have value counts equals or less than 5 (Set None)
def Replace_brands(df):
    counts = df['brand_name'].value_counts()
    small_counts = counts[counts <= 5].index
    df['brand_name'] = df['brand_name'].replace(small_counts, None)

dfs = [thoitrang,dien,mobile]
for df in dfs:
    Replace_brands(df)

**Gi :** Sn phm ca danh mc IN GIA DNG c gi trung bnh cao nht (2.83 triu), theo sau l IN THOI MY TNH BNG (~5.9 triu) v THI TRANG NAM c gi trung bnh thp nht (0.25 triu). S chnh lch ny c th phn nh s khc bit v gi tr, cht lng v nhu cu ca ngi tiu dng i vi cc loi sn phm ny.


**Discount rate :** IN THOI MY TNH BNG li dn u vi mc gim gi trung bnh cao nht (0.94 triu), theo sau l IN GIA DNG (~0.32 triu) v THI TRANG NAM c mc gim gi trung bnh thp nht (0.016 triu). iu ny c th cho thy rng ngnh cng nghip di ng c xu hng s dng chit khu gi nh mt phng php tip th ph bin hn.


**Rating average :** Ngi tiu dng nh gi sn phm IN THOI MY TNH BNG cao nht vi im nh gi trung bnh l 10.73, trong khi IN GIA DNG v THI TRANG NAM c im nh gi trung bnh thp hn, ln lt l 6.5 v 4.0.


**S lng bn :** IN THOI MY TNH BNG cng dn u vi s lng sn phm bn ra trung bnh l 239, so vi 55 cho IN GIA DNG v ch 29 cho THI TRANG NAM. iu ny c th phn nh s chnh lch v mc  ph bin ca cc sn phm ny trong s ngi tiu dng.


Nhn chung, mi danh mc sn phm u c nhng im mnh ring. Sn phm THI TRANG NAM c gi trung bnh thp, ph hp vi ngi tiu dng c ngn sch hn hp. IN GIA DNG tuy c gi trung bnh cao hn, nhng cung cp mc gim gi ng k. Trong khi , IN THOI MY TNH BNG nhn c nh gi cao t ngi tiu dng v c s lng bn ra ng ch , cho thy cht lng sn phm tt v s hi lng ca khch hng.

dataframes = [thoitrang, dien, mobile]
titles = ["THI TRANG", "IN GIA DNG", "IN THOI - MY TNH BNG"]

for df, title in zip(dataframes, titles):
    corr_matrix = df.corr()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

import statsmodels.api as sm
dataframes = [thoitrang, dien, mobile]
titles = ["THI TRANG", "IN GIA DNG", "IN THOI - MY TNH BNG"]

for df, title in zip(dataframes, titles):
    print(title)
    X = df.drop(['quantity_sold','name','brand_name'],axis = 1)
    y = df['quantity_sold']
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()
    print(model.summary())
    print()
    print('*'*80)
    print('*'*80)
    print()

# Using T-test

from scipy.stats import ttest_ind
dataframes = [thoitrang, dien, mobile]
titles = ["THI TRANG", "IN GIA DNG", "IN THOI - MY TNH BNG"]

for df, title in zip(dataframes, titles):
    print(title)
    high_discount = df[df['discount_rate'] > 50]['quantity_sold']
    low_discount = df[df['discount_rate'] <= 10]['quantity_sold']
    t_stat, p_value = ttest_ind(high_discount, low_discount, equal_var=False)

    print('t statistic:', t_stat)
    print('p value:', p_value)
    print("----------------------------------\n\n")

def plot_data(title, sold_data, not_sold_data, variables=['discount_rate', 'price']):
    print(title.upper())

    groups = [sold_data, not_sold_data]
    group_labels = ['sold', 'not sold']

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize=(10, 10))

    for i, variable in enumerate(variables):
        for j, group in enumerate(groups):
            sns.violinplot(data=group, x=variable, ax=axes[i, j])
            axes[i, j].set_title(f'{variable} - {group_labels[j]}')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

plot_data("Thi trang nam", thoitrang_sold, thoitrang_not_sold)
print('*'*90)
plot_data("in gia dng", dien_sold, dien_not_sold)
print('*'*90)
plot_data("in thoi my tnh bng", mobile_sold, mobile_not_sold)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def plot_pie(title, sold_data, not_sold_data, col='brand_name'):
    print(title.upper())

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(14, 7))

    top_5_sold = sold_data[col].value_counts().head(5)
    top_5_not_sold = not_sold_data[col].value_counts().head(5)

    explode = [0.1 if i == 1 else 0 for i in range(5)]
    palette_color = sns.color_palette('pastel')

    axes[0].pie(top_5_sold.values, labels=top_5_sold.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', explode=explode, colors=palette_color)
    axes[0].set_title('Top 5 brands - sold')
    
    axes[1].pie(top_5_not_sold.values, labels=top_5_not_sold.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', explode=explode, colors=palette_color)
    axes[1].set_title('Top 5 brands - not sold')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


plot_pie("Thi trang nam", thoitrang_sold, thoitrang_not_sold)
plot_pie("in gia dng", dien_sold, dien_not_sold)
plot_pie("in thoi my tnh bng", mobile_sold, mobile_not_sold)

def split_dataframe(df):
    top_10percent_index = int(len(df) * 0.1)
    bottom_10percent_index = len(df) - top_10percent_index

    df_head = df.iloc[:top_10percent_index]
    df_tail = df.iloc[bottom_10percent_index:]
    
    return df_head, df_tail

thoitrang_head, thoitrang_tail = split_dataframe(tt_rate)
dien_head, dien_tail = split_dataframe(dien_rate)
mobile_head, mobile_tail = split_dataframe(mobile_rate)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def plot_pie(title, sold_data, not_sold_data, col='brand_name'):
    print(title.upper())

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(14, 7))

    top_5_sold = sold_data[col].value_counts().head(5)
    top_5_not_sold = not_sold_data[col].value_counts().head(5)

    explode = [0.1 if i == 1 else 0 for i in range(5)]
    palette_color = sns.color_palette('pastel')

    axes[0].pie(top_5_sold.values, labels=top_5_sold.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', explode=explode, colors=palette_color)
    axes[0].set_title('Top 5 brands - High Rate')
    
    axes[1].pie(top_5_not_sold.values, labels=top_5_not_sold.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', explode=explode, colors=palette_color)
    axes[1].set_title('Top 5 brands - Low Rate')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()


plot_pie("Thi trang nam", thoitrang_head, thoitrang_tail)

def plot_data(title, high_data, low_data, variables=['discount_rate', 'original_price']):
    print(title.upper())

    groups = [high_data, low_data]
    group_labels = ['High Rate', 'Low Rate']

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize=(10, 10))

    for i, variable in enumerate(variables):
        for j, group in enumerate(groups):
            sns.violinplot(data=group, x=variable, ax=axes[i, j])
            axes[i, j].set_title(f'{variable} - {group_labels[j]}')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

plot_data("Thi trang nam", thoitrang_head, thoitrang_tail)
plot_data("in gia dng", dien_head, dien_tail)
plot_data("in thoi my tnh bng", mobile_head, mobile_tail)
